dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The "ICES Divisions" Feature Class layer has been sourced from the International Council for the Exploration of the Seas (ie. ICES) organisation in Denmark. Further information on the work of ICES and available datasets is obtainable from their website @ http://www.ices.dk.
This layer is used extensively by Fisheries Science Services in the Marine Institute when collecting and reporting on fisheries data. The layer is a very useful basemap layer for dividing ocean waters into zones for further analysis.
The geometry accuracy reflects the ICES divisions based on the UTM Latitude Longitude grid.

Consts.useLimit: There are no known data use restrictions.
